  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large bowl, combine the yam, carrots, red onion, zucchini, garlic, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper. Toss to coat.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and roast for 25 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, in a small bowl, whisk together the orange marmalade, coconut oil, and curry powder.",
    "To assemble the wraps, place 1-2 tablespoons of the roasted vegetable mixture on the center of each corn husk, leaving a 1-inch border around the edges.",
    "Drizzle 1-2 tablespoons of the marmalade mixture over the vegetables and fold the bottom edge of the corn husk up over the filling.",
    "Fold in the sides and then roll the wrap up tightly to form a compact cylinder.",
    "Repeat with the remaining ingredients and serve warm."
  ],
